The paper proposes a novel Multi-Task Learning framework based on Support Vector Machines for binary classification tasks. The paper discusses the use of feature spaces and task affinity, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The empirical evaluation involves seven datasets, which suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
